\f0\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::2><$Scr_Ps::0>
\f1\b\fs32 Current
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\fs32  refers to the flow of electric charge in an electrical circuit. It is the rate at which electric charges, typically electrons, move through a 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\b\fs32 conductor
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\fs32 . Electrons, which are negatively charged particles, are the primary carriers of electric charge in most conductive materials.
\f3\fs28 \cf3 \
\pard\sb40\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf3 <!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>
