\f0\fs24 \cf2 <!$Scr_Ps::1><$Scr_Ps::0>
\f2\fs32 Current is measured in amperes (A) and is represented by the symbol I. It can be thought of as the quantity of charge passing through a point in a circuit per unit of time, or alternately as the rate of charge flow. \
The 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\b\fs32 ampere
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\fs32 , or 
\f0\fs24 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f1\b\fs32 amp
\f0\b0\fs24 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f2\fs32  (unit symbol: A) is the unit of electrical current.  One ampere is equal to one coulomb of charge moving past a point in one second.\
\pard\sb40\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\fs24 \cf3 <!$Scr_Ps::0><$Scr_Ps::1>
